{
  "stem": "20021.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father was sort of-- he didn't wear a beard and he didn't wear his Tzitzit, which is called the fringes, you know, clothes with fringes.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He didn't wear it outside, while others did.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I would say half the population in Tarnow were very strict Orthodox Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Today they would be called Hasidic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they would wear their fringes outwardly, because that supposedly is the command of the Torah, that you should wear them in a way where everybody can see them.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They would be observing everything to the minutest detail.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Nowhere would males and females pray together in the same room.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Females would always be separate and so forth.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Women would have to wear long dress.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Even young girls would have to wear long sleeves, modest dresses buttoned up all the way top, and legs not exposed and so forth and so forth.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] on Rosh Hashanah and Yom Kippur, everybody went to a synagogue, even the non-observant and the non-religious.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Nobody would dare think not to go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But on an average Sabbath, I would say probably 70%, something like that I'm guessing, certainly more than half of the Jews would go to synagogue to pray.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My family went every Saturday to synagogue.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I followed with my father to synagogue, every Saturday.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I remember the prayers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember the-- the camaraderie.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "During the prayers, every-- you had to know where.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Certain passages you would stop talking.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But there were certain passages which were considered less important and you would allow yourself to talk.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it was sort of also a way of socializing during prayers, you know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when I was very young, I would play in the yard there outside the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
